employment rate like
this actually indicates

10
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:44,375
is that many people have given
up looking for work at all.

11
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:45,916
And those who aren't
actively seeking

12
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,833
out jobs aren't counted
as being unemployed,

13
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:51,208
so, as a result, the
unemployment rate goes down.

14
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:52,500
Also--

15
00:00:52,583 --> 00:00:53,750
[TWENTY FACES 9A]
Think about it.

16
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:55,208
The big shots are the
ones who play dirtiest

