247
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:41,125
There's no doubt if Akechi's
loses this showdown,

248
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:43,416
the number of Twenty
Faces will explode.

249
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,875
[HASHIBA]
Kobayashi!

250
00:12:44,958 --> 00:12:46,958
Hey, are you listening?!

251
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:50,625
[gasps] Yeah, sure. What's up?

252
00:12:50,708 --> 00:12:52,333
I'm just worried.

253
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:54,625
Weren't you absent from
school again today?

254
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:57,958
Ah... Yeah.

255
00:12:58,041 --> 00:13:00,333
I mean, we've already
figured out the formula.

256
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:01,708
You should be in class.

257
00:13:01,791 --> 00:13:02,958
Uh...

258
00:13:03,041 --> 00:13:03,958
[HASHIBA]
If you keep this up,

259
00:13:04,041 --> 00:13:06,625
people are going
to start talking.

260
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:08,500
So? That doesn't
really bother me.

261
00:13:08,583 --> 00:13:09,041
[KITTEN]
Meow.

262
00:13:09,125 --> 00:13:10,208
[HASHIBA sighs]

263
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,000
How come it's such a big deal?

264
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:15,375
Why are you so freaked out

265
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:17,875
about me missing some
school here and there?

266
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:20,625
C'mon, don't you think
that's obvious?!

267
00:13:20,708 --> 00:13:22,458
What's obvious?

268
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:26,916
Hashiba?

269
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:28,791
What's wrong?

270
00:13:32,916 --> 00:13:35,333
Kobayashi...

271
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,583
[DOCTOR A]
It's been a while, hasn't it?

272
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:47,958
[DOCTOR AA]
Yes.

273
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:49,666
And I hear that Dr. Munakata
is the guest of honor.

274
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:52,041
[DOCTOR B] I've never heard of
the organizer, though, have you?

275
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:55,666
[DOCTOR C] So, what is
today's party for, anyway?

276
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,208
[applause]

277
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:06,583
Wow.

278
00:14:06,666 --> 00:14:08,958
Isn't it wonderful to see so
many familiar faces today?

279
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:10,791
Thanks to all of you
for coming out.

280
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:12,125
Well, I'll get right to it.

281
00:14:12,208 --> 00:14:14,125
The steady decline of
physicians' ethics

282
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:16,750
has come under scrutiny
in the media recently.

283
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:20,083
Illegal practices, malpractice
cover-ups, you name it.

284
00:14:20,166 --> 00:14:21,500
That's why I'm so grateful

285
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:23,916
that I'm to be presented with
the People's Honor Award

286
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,666
in recognition of my numerous
achievements in the field.

287
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:28,291
To receive recognition
for my years

288
00:14:28,375 --> 00:14:30,958
of upright practices
and patient care--

289
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:32,666
--[CROWD murmurs]
--[DOCTOR CC] A blackout?

290
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:34,125
[DOCTOR C]
A blackout?

291
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:35,875
[DOCTOR D]
What's happening?

292
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,208
[MUNAKATA gasps]

293
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,750
This is...

294
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,875
[ALTERED VOICE] I present,
leading brain surgeon,

295
00:14:45,958 --> 00:14:47,833
Ryuichiro Munakata.

296
00:14:47,916 --> 00:14:50,625
Behind his shiny façade
and apparent glory,

297
00:14:50,708 --> 00:14:53,125
there is a darkness hidden
deep beneath the surface.

298
00:14:53,208 --> 00:14:54,041
[DOCTOR A]
What's going on?

299
00:14:54,125 --> 00:14:55,166
[DOCTOR AA]
Darkness?

300
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:57,125
[DOCTOR B]
What are they talking about?

301
00:14:59,166 --> 00:15:01,333
[MUNAKATA gasping]

302
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:09,333
[BROTHER] On the day I first
developed symptoms...

303
00:15:11,916 --> 00:15:13,791
[BROTHER]
I was sentenced to die.

304
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:17,916
He told me that I might
have a year, if I was lucky.

305
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,666
[MUNAKATA]
I'm very sorry.

306
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,541
[SISTER] This couldn't have
just happened naturally!

307
00:15:21,625 --> 00:15:23,166
There's gotta be more to it!

308
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,000
[MUNAKATA] It's true that
he's young for this disease

309
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:29,500
to develop, but it's
definitely not unheard of.

310
00:15:33,125 --> 00:15:34,375
[BROTHER]
It's not his fault.

311
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:36,708
Sis, he actually saved my life.

312
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:38,000
The surgery.

313
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,791
I'd already be dead without it.

314
00:15:39,875 --> 00:15:41,958
I owe him everything.

315
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:44,333
[BROTHER]
My sister did some research

316
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:47,000
and dug through the internal
records of the hospital.

317
00:15:47,083 --> 00:15:49,833
She found out that uncontrolled
dura mater obtained through

318
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:53,875
illegal channels was used
for several surgeries.

319
00:15:53,958 --> 00:15:56,333
This dura mater was also
used in the surgery

320
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,916
Dr. Munakata performed on me.

321
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,833
It was the source
of the infection

322
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:03,583
that was slowly killing me.

323
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:08,541
[MUNAKATA]
That's a false accusation.

324
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:10,666
The data you found is
a recording error.

325
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:12,541
It's as simple as that.

326
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:16,041
[BROTHER]
My medical record, the evidence.

327
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,791
Everything conclusive was
quickly and conveniently

328
00:16:18,875 --> 00:16:21,000
swept under the rug.

329
00:16:26,083 --> 00:16:29,833
[BROTHER]
Oh, sis. Please don't cry.

330
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:33,250
And that's... that's why I...

331
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:39,416
[BROTHER]
I wish...

332
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,666
[DOCTOR C]
Oh, boy.

333
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:50,791
[DOCTOR D]
Is that really true?

334
00:16:50,875 --> 00:16:52,666
[MUNAKATA]
No! This is a horrible lie!

335
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:55,000
I swear, someone's
trying to frame me!

336
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:56,500
[SISTER]
Oh, it's true!

337
00:16:56,583 --> 00:17:00,000
And I should know, because
that boy was my little brother!

338
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,750
[CROWD gasps]

339
00:17:04,458 --> 00:17:05,416
[ALL gasp]

340
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,375
[SISTER]
You ready?

341
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:08,708
Meet this week's Twenty Faces.

342
00:17:08,791 --> 00:17:12,083
Surprise, it's me!

343
00:17:12,166 --> 00:17:15,000
[ALTERED VOICE] We've been right
beside you for quite some time,

344
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:17,083
but you never see.

345
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:18,875
[SISTER]
Yeah!

346
00:17:18,958 --> 00:17:19,916
Wait. Aren't you the...?

347
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,416
[MINAMI]
I'm Medical Examiner Minami!

348
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,125
And this is
Three-Minute Shocking!

349
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,458
Today's menu is...

350
00:17:24,541 --> 00:17:25,833
This!

351
00:17:25,916 --> 00:17:27,500
The same stuff that was used
for my brother's surgery

352
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,583
is in the food that you were
served for lunch today!

353
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:32,125
Was it super tasty?
I sure hope so!

354
00:17:32,208 --> 00:17:33,916
[gasps]

355
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,250
[MINAMI] Of course, you're
a smarty pants doctor.

356
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,041
So, you already know
that stuff's dangerous

357
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:39,500
even when ingested orally!

358
00:17:39,583 --> 00:17:41,416
[DOCTOR A]
Wait, that's not true, is it?

359
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,916
[DOCTOR AA screams]
I ate it, I ate it!

360
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,250
[MUNAKATA]
This is unbelievable!

361
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:46,208
I'm a genius!

362
00:17:46,291 --> 00:17:47,541
You're depriving future mankind

363
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:50,208
of countless contributions
to the field!

364
00:17:50,291 --> 00:17:52,500
This is a desecration of
modern medical science!

365
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:54,333
[MINAMI]
Punishment Punch!

366
00:17:54,416 --> 00:17:55,750
[MUNAKATA groans]

367
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:59,833
[MINAMI] Oh doc, you truly
are pathetic, aren't you?

368
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:02,541
You did this exact same
thing to your patients,

369
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:04,791
but turn the tables
and you fall to pieces.

370
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:07,208
[MUNAKATA] I've got to
go test for infection!

371
00:18:07,291 --> 00:18:08,666
[AKECHI]
That won't be necessary.

372
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:09,875
[MINAMI. MANAKATA gasp]

373
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:19,208
[REPORTER 9B] So that woman
is Twenty Faces this time?

374
00:18:19,291 --> 00:18:21,250
[MINAMI laughs]

375
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,375
You're way too late, Akechi!

376
00:18:23,458 --> 00:18:25,833
You didn't get
here fast enough!

377
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:28,791
Looks like the damage
has already been done!

378
00:18:28,875 --> 00:18:31,958
'Fraid not. You haven't been
able to do a damn thing.

379
00:18:32,041 --> 00:18:33,291
[MINAMI]
Huh?

380
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:35,458
[AKECHI] They didn't
eat any of it, Minami.

381
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,458
I had all the food in
this hall replaced

382
00:18:37,541 --> 00:18:39,458
with safe food well beforehand.

383
00:18:39,541 --> 00:18:40,500
[MINAMI growls]

384
00:18:41,541 --> 00:18:42,958
The police have
already surrounded

385
00:18:43,041 --> 00:18:45,083
the conference room
and the building.

386
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:47,416
Looks like you won't be
doing any damage at all.

387
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,916
You'll be arrested before
you have a chance.

388
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,208
It's a definitive defeat.

389
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:56,750
[MINAMI] I see. So, you've
finally figured it out, then.

390
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:59,041
I mean Dark Star, of course.

391
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:00,250
That's right.

392
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,375
This is the end of Twenty Faces.

393
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:03,583
Once and for all.

394
00:19:03,666 --> 00:19:07,500
[MINAMI laughs]

395
00:19:13,625 --> 00:19:15,083
What's funny?

396
00:19:15,166 --> 00:19:17,291
[MINAMI] I already knew this
was going to happen, you idiot.

397
00:19:17,375 --> 00:19:18,708
[AKECHI]
What?

398
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:20,625
[CROWD murmurs]

399
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:26,416
[SKULL MAN] You're really
here, aren't you...

400
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:27,625
Akechi?

401
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:28,875
[AKECHI gasps]

402
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:30,833
[REPORTER C]
Another Twenty Faces?

403
00:19:30,916 --> 00:19:32,583
[REPORTER D]
Is that Southern Terrace?

404
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:36,125
[MINAMI laughs]
The media rushing in here

405
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,625
and my defeat are only
part of the larger plan!

406
00:19:38,708 --> 00:19:40,541
Every bit of this is
in the chain of events

407
00:19:40,625 --> 00:19:41,916
that the formula predicts!

408
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,708
Akechi, hold on!

409
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:50,458
[AKECHI panting]

410
00:20:39,083 --> 00:20:42,458
[panting] You killed him!

411
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:44,750
[SKULL MAN]
It was an accident.

412
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:48,125
[CROWD screaming]

413
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:50,333
[DOCTOR AA]
Mr. Munakata!

414
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,041
[SKULL MAN]
The world we live in is a dream.

415
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:56,333
The dream we have at
night is the true world.

416
00:20:58,541 --> 00:21:00,333
Namikoshi.

417
00:21:01,166 --> 00:21:03,125
[REPORTER 9A]
What? Namikoshi?

418
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:05,500
[REPORTER 9C]
It must be make-up, right?

419
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:08,458
[REPORTER 9D] I thought
he was burned to death!

420
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:10,333
[MAN 9C]
What's this?

421
00:21:13,166 --> 00:21:14,583
[POLICE OFFICER A]
What's going on?

422
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:18,000
[MINAMI laughs]
All of this happened

423
00:21:18,083 --> 00:21:22,083
only to herald his
miraculous return to us!

424
00:21:27,125 --> 00:21:30,416
Twenty Faces isn't
some cult myth.

425
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:32,250
It's our reality.

